Title: Adding support for $count segment in $filter collections in OData WebAPI
Description: Introduction In OData core  v7.9.0 we added improved support for $count segment in $filter collection properties. $filter=navProp/$count($filter=prop gt 1) gt 2 $filter=collectionProp/$count($filter=prop gt 1) gt 2 Previously, versions of OData core had support for: $filter=navProp/$count gt 2 $filter=collectionProp/$count gt 2 We are constantly improving filtering capabilities in OData WebAPI.

Title: Support for fetching nested paths in OData Web API
Description: Background OData services use nested paths to access properties or entities related to a resource. For example, if you want to access orders of a given customer, you would use a request path like: http://localhost:8080/Customers/1/Orders Microsoft.AspNetCore.OData 7.x provides two main approaches for handling such requests: convention and attribute routing.
